section.section:
The Central Repository shall store the following domestic violence orders issued in the State:
interim protective orders;
temporary protective orders;
final protective orders;
peace orders issued under Title 3, Subtitle 15 of the Courts Article; and
except as provided in paragraph (2) of this subsection, peace orders issued under Title 3, Subtitle 8A of the Courts Article.

text.section:
The purposes of the Central Repository are to:
provide immediate access to domestic violence orders by judges, court personnel, and law enforcement agencies;
improve the courts' ability to respond effectively, promptly, and in a coordinated manner to domestic violence cases;
eliminate conflicting or simultaneous domestic violence orders by improving communication between the District Court and the circuit courts;
enhance the enforceability of domestic violence orders by law enforcement agencies; and
facilitate service of domestic violence orders.
